"Before We Were Born" painting by Meagan Boyd @yinshadowz 〰️ .
.
"I made this piece as a sort of love poem to my husband. We have always said that we've known each other even before we were born. I started to envision what our spirits must have looked like then. Sometimes I think we might have been part of the same thing, just split in two. Somehow we found each other despite being born in different countries. I promised I'd meet him in the next life in the same place we met in this one. Maybe it's not just us- we're all connected but some more than others, and only some can really recognize it. Looking into someone and seeing yourself. This cosmic serpent is slithering up into a conch shell, like a sperm swims into an egg. It comes from two hands and there's strange birds, one to the right and one to the left. Each its own entity but connected through this cosmic snake that transcends time and space." - Meagan Boyd
